{
  "texts": [
    "The posterior median of τ gr is reported as the final point estimate.",
    "We clean the sample of best-fit EzTaoX and JAVELIN lags by removing those associated with nonconvergent MCMC chains.",
    "Specifically, we discard fits in which the MCMC chain for τ gr yields fewer than 400 effective samples (n eff), following the recommendation of Vehtari et al. (2021) for selecting converged chains.",
    "Approximately 20% of the 3-year and 7% of the 10-year EzTaoX fits are removed by this criterion, while ∼20% of the JAVELIN fits are removed from both the 3-year and 10-year data.",
    "Examined as a function of the input τ gr, the fraction of discarded JAVELIN fits increases with increasing true τ gr; in contrast, the fraction of discarded EzTaoX fits remains relatively constant across the range of input τ gr."
  ]
}